{"id": "general-chat--hardware--t1000e-support", "title": "t1000e support", "forum": "General Chat", "messages": [{"id": "1354328749948010506", "author": "Memo", "author_handle": "memo.randum", "user_id": "1349369108705181717", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1349369108705181717/be7799fd20975cb55e4159cfbc68b5da.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Wednesday, March 26, 2025 1:38 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-03-26 1:38 a.m.", "text": "The T1000E worked for a long time (hours?) without any problems. When I tried to pair smartphone B instead of smartphone A, it no longer worked (the LED also remained off). Even pressing the button didn't help. After a few tries it seemed to work by pressing the button and connecting the charging plug.", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>The T1000E worked for a long time (hours?) without any problems. When I tried to pair smartphone B instead of smartphone A, it no longer worked (the LED also remained off).\nEven pressing the button didn&#39;t help. After a few tries it seemed to work by pressing the button and connecting the charging plug.</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1354331040885379175", "author": "Memo", "author_handle": "memo.randum", "user_id": "1349369108705181717", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1349369108705181717/be7799fd20975cb55e4159cfbc68b5da.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Wednesday, March 26, 2025 1:48 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-03-26 1:48 a.m.", "text": "When attempting to access repeater remote management, the connection also breaks. (edited)", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>When attempting to access repeater remote management, the connection also breaks.</span> <span class=chatlog__edited-timestamp title=\"Wednesday, March 26, 2025 2:16 a.m.\">(edited)</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1354771819906732224", "author": "Memo", "author_handle": "memo.randum", "user_id": "1349369108705181717", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1349369108705181717/be7799fd20975cb55e4159cfbc68b5da.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Thursday, March 27, 2025 6:59 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-03-27 6:59 a.m.", "text": "Switch between phones Repeater admin login", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Switch between phones  <img\n    loading=\"lazy\"\n    class=\"chatlog__emoji \"\n    alt=\"✅\"\n    title=\"white_check_mark\"\n    src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/2705.svg\">\nRepeater admin login  <img\n    loading=\"lazy\"\n    class=\"chatlog__emoji \"\n    alt=\"✅\"\n    title=\"white_check_mark\"\n    src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/2705.svg\"></span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "<div class=chatlog__reactions><div class=chatlog__reaction title=thumbsup><img class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--small\" alt=👍 src=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f44d.svg loading=lazy> <span class=chatlog__reaction-count>1</span></div></div>", "reply_html": "<div class=chatlog__reply><img class=chatlog__reply-avatar src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1339177107024248872/2a0b0eebeada9b98e9f1c5ee2bfc98d2.png?size=512\" alt=Avatar loading=lazy><div class=chatlog__reply-author style=color:rgb(231,76,60) title=fdlamotte_33640>FDLamotte</div><div class=chatlog__reply-content><span class=chatlog__reply-link onclick=\"scrollToMessage(event,'1354764142283718787')\"> here is the beta ... </span></div></div>", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1354835689333850354", "author": "Memo", "author_handle": "memo.randum", "user_id": "1349369108705181717", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1349369108705181717/be7799fd20975cb55e4159cfbc68b5da.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Thursday, March 27, 2025 11:13 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-03-27 11:13 a.m.", "text": "Already updated", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Already updated  <img\n    loading=\"lazy\"\n    class=\"chatlog__emoji \"\n    alt=\"😉\"\n    title=\"wink\"\n    src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f609.svg\"></span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1354891241300430899", "author": "DemoMan", "author_handle": "demoman_63", "user_id": "694827601486807120", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Thursday, March 27, 2025 2:54 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-03-27 2:54 p.m.", "text": "Hi @FDLamotte , I installed your latest firmware, but the serial connection isn't working, and the T1000 can no longer be turned off by holding the button for 5 seconds. I tried flashing it twice, but it still didn’t work. The previous version works fine.", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Hi <span class=\"chatlog__markdown-mention\" title=\"fdlamotte_33640\">@FDLamotte</span> , I installed your latest firmware, but the serial connection isn&#39;t working, and the T1000 can no longer be turned off by holding the button for 5 seconds. I tried flashing it twice, but it still didn’t work. The previous version works fine.</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "<div class=chatlog__reply><img class=chatlog__reply-avatar src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1339177107024248872/2a0b0eebeada9b98e9f1c5ee2bfc98d2.png?size=512\" alt=Avatar loading=lazy><div class=chatlog__reply-author style=color:rgb(231,76,60) title=fdlamotte_33640>FDLamotte</div><div class=chatlog__reply-content><span class=chatlog__reply-link onclick=\"scrollToMessage(event,'1354830389222309889')\"> made the release with the code I sent this morning, busy with new rak boards <img\n    loading=\"lazy\"\n    class=\"chatlog__emoji \"\n    alt=\"😉\"\n    title=\"wink\"\n    src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f609.svg\">\n<a href=\"https://github.com/fdlamotte/MeshCoreT1000e/releases/tag/2025-03-27\">https://github.com/fdlamotte/MeshCoreT1000e/releases/tag/2025-03-27</a> </span></div></div>", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1354896315108032654", "author": "DemoMan", "author_handle": "demoman_63", "user_id": "694827601486807120", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Thursday, March 27, 2025 3:14 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-03-27 3:14 p.m.", "text": "I was using serial console from WebFlasher", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>I was using serial console from WebFlasher</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1354902643335630980", "author": "DemoMan", "author_handle": "demoman_63", "user_id": "694827601486807120", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Thursday, March 27, 2025 3:39 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-03-27 3:39 p.m.", "text": "Now is working fine , I try all commands and all works ok.", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Now is working fine , I try all commands and all works ok.</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "<div class=chatlog__reactions><div class=chatlog__reaction title=thumbsup><img class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--small\" alt=👍 src=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f44d.svg loading=lazy> <span class=chatlog__reaction-count>2</span></div></div>", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1356170277200855041", "author": "Memo", "author_handle": "memo.randum", "user_id": "1349369108705181717", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1349369108705181717/be7799fd20975cb55e4159cfbc68b5da.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Monday, March 31, 2025 3:36 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-03-31 3:36 a.m.", "text": "59% after 15h 48m here with 2025-03-30", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>59% after 15h 48m here with 2025-03-30</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "<div class=chatlog__reactions><div class=chatlog__reaction title=thumbsup><img class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--small\" alt=👍 src=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f44d.svg loading=lazy> <span class=chatlog__reaction-count>1</span></div></div>", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1356171286040023081", "author": "Memo", "author_handle": "memo.randum", "user_id": "1349369108705181717", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1349369108705181717/be7799fd20975cb55e4159cfbc68b5da.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Monday, March 31, 2025 3:40 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-03-31 3:40 a.m.", "text": "That's a nice idea", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>That&#39;s a nice idea  <img\n    loading=\"lazy\"\n    class=\"chatlog__emoji \"\n    alt=\"😀\"\n    title=\"grinning\"\n    src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f600.svg\"></span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1356516111436218409", "author": "Memo", "author_handle": "memo.randum", "user_id": "1349369108705181717", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1349369108705181717/be7799fd20975cb55e4159cfbc68b5da.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Tuesday, April 1, 2025 2:30 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-04-01 2:30 a.m.", "text": "Apart from the repeater (and soon also the room server), I usually turn off my companion devices at night. I've even installed a manual switch for this purpose. With the exception of the T1000E, these cannot yet be switched off via the FW.", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Apart from the repeater (and soon also the room server), I usually turn off my companion devices at night. I&#39;ve even installed a manual switch for this purpose. With the exception of the T1000E, these cannot yet be switched off via the FW.</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": ["<div class=chatlog__attachment><a href=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1354192415845519400/1356516111239352473/20250328_132719-01.jpeg?ex=69ebb6d3&amp;is=69ea6553&amp;hm=85155fdcd64ca8ce8a0bb4cf7a5545409805cf8e847223022b9319c7650d57d0&amp;\"> <img class=chatlog__attachment-media src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1354192415845519400/1356516111239352473/20250328_132719-01.jpeg?ex=69ebb6d3&amp;is=69ea6553&amp;hm=85155fdcd64ca8ce8a0bb4cf7a5545409805cf8e847223022b9319c7650d57d0&amp;\" alt=\"Image attachment\" title=\"Image: 20250328_132719-01.jpeg (826.11 KB)\" loading=lazy> </a></div>"], "reactions_html": "<div class=chatlog__reactions><div class=chatlog__reaction title=thumbsup><img class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--small\" alt=👍 src=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f44d.svg loading=lazy> <span class=chatlog__reaction-count>2</span></div></div>", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1356541113334366258", "author": "Memo", "author_handle": "memo.randum", "user_id": "1349369108705181717", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1349369108705181717/be7799fd20975cb55e4159cfbc68b5da.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Tuesday, April 1, 2025 4:10 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-04-01 4:10 a.m.", "text": "The main reason for the physical switch was the desire to change the antenna - without dismantling the entire device.", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>The main reason for the physical switch was the desire to change the antenna - without dismantling the entire device.</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1360312501299839007", "author": "DemoMan", "author_handle": "demoman_63", "user_id": "694827601486807120", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Friday, April 11, 2025 1:56 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-04-11 1:56 p.m.", "text": "What did you set to off on the T1000 for this power usage ?", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>What did you set to off on the T1000 for this power usage ?</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1360316570794066011", "author": "DemoMan", "author_handle": "demoman_63", "user_id": "694827601486807120", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Friday, April 11, 2025 2:12 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-04-11 2:12 p.m.", "text": "Yeah, I use RX_Boost on the MT, and there's an average difference of about 2 dBi in reception. Maybe it would make more sense if RX_Boost could be turned off during sleep mode, and then turned back on again when the device wakes up... would that be logical?", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Yeah, I use RX_Boost on the MT, and there&#39;s an average difference of about 2 dBi in reception. Maybe it would make more sense if RX_Boost could be turned off during sleep mode, and then turned back on again when the device wakes up... would that be logical?</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1361325683325796542", "author": "Memo", "author_handle": "memo.randum", "user_id": "1349369108705181717", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1349369108705181717/be7799fd20975cb55e4159cfbc68b5da.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Monday, April 14, 2025 9:02 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-04-14 9:02 a.m.", "text": "I'm curious. The T1000E is my everyday node for close range. So the longer it lasts, the better - if everything else works", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>I&#39;m curious. The T1000E is my everyday node for close range.\nSo the longer it lasts, the better - if everything else works  <img\n    loading=\"lazy\"\n    class=\"chatlog__emoji \"\n    alt=\"😉\"\n    title=\"wink\"\n    src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f609.svg\"></span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1361329905303945457", "author": "Memo", "author_handle": "memo.randum", "user_id": "1349369108705181717", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1349369108705181717/be7799fd20975cb55e4159cfbc68b5da.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Monday, April 14, 2025 9:19 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-04-14 9:19 a.m.", "text": "", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve><img\n    loading=\"lazy\"\n    class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--large\"\n    alt=\"😂\"\n    title=\"joy\"\n    src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f602.svg\"></span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "<div class=chatlog__reply><img class=chatlog__reply-avatar src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1339177107024248872/2a0b0eebeada9b98e9f1c5ee2bfc98d2.png?size=512\" alt=Avatar loading=lazy><div class=chatlog__reply-author style=color:rgb(231,76,60) title=fdlamotte_33640>FDLamotte</div><div class=chatlog__reply-content><span class=chatlog__reply-link onclick=\"scrollToMessage(event,'1361329547328618647')\"> I am curious too <img\n    loading=\"lazy\"\n    class=\"chatlog__emoji \"\n    alt=\"😉\"\n    title=\"wink\"\n    src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f609.svg\"> </span></div></div>", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1361331023006404819", "author": "Memo", "author_handle": "memo.randum", "user_id": "1349369108705181717", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1349369108705181717/be7799fd20975cb55e4159cfbc68b5da.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Monday, April 14, 2025 9:23 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-04-14 9:23 a.m.", "text": "I don't know if I've shown you this picture before, but I love that this little thing fits so nicely in my phone case.", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>I don&#39;t know if I&#39;ve shown you this picture before, but I love that this little thing fits so nicely in my phone case.</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": ["<div class=chatlog__attachment><a href=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1354192415845519400/1361331022750290112/P1070747-01_wm.jpg?ex=69ec1790&amp;is=69eac610&amp;hm=e2bc89c4e09c6ff939d2faf3d80323307bf2412d88b79351024c2d4c51340469&amp;\"> <img class=chatlog__attachment-media src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1354192415845519400/1361331022750290112/P1070747-01_wm.jpg?ex=69ec1790&amp;is=69eac610&amp;hm=e2bc89c4e09c6ff939d2faf3d80323307bf2412d88b79351024c2d4c51340469&amp;\" alt=\"Image attachment\" title=\"Image: P1070747-01_wm.jpg (492.77 KB)\" loading=lazy> </a></div>"], "reactions_html": "<div class=chatlog__reactions><div class=chatlog__reaction title=heart><img class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--small\" alt=❤️ src=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/2764.svg loading=lazy> <span class=chatlog__reaction-count>1</span></div></div>", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "136156160557